A New York man killed his grandmother during an argument over what TV show to watch, police say.

Clarence Newcomb, 25, was reportedly arrested on Friday at the home he shared with Kathleen Newcomb, 82, in Kings Park, on Long Island about 40 miles east of New York City.

Local police say a man called them at about 4:35 a.m. to report the woman was lying on the floor.

